  "description": "Note **Not available in FLAC2D . The Mohr-Coulomb model is not well suited for simulation of tensile failure (fracturing). One non-physical behavior of the Mohr-Coulomb constitutive model regarding the tensile failure is that the tensile plastic strain, \\(\\varepsilon^p_i\\) , is irreversible. Consequently, any reversal of the plastic strain that caused failure in tension results in immediate generation of the compressive stresses. Typically, the irreversible part of the tensile plastic strain in the geological materials is relatively small (i.e., can be assumed to be zero). In other words, tens",
